Date: Tue, 14 Apr 2026 18:32:09 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Expose dataset graph edge details and feedback weight updates

The local memify workflow needs two dataset-level graph capabilities:
full edge metadata on graph reads and a bulk feedback-weight update
endpoint on graph writes. This commit adds both so clients can fade
or promote nodes and edges without reaching into adapter internals.

Constraint: Must work with the existing dataset permission model and graph engine interfaces
Rejected: Expose adapter methods directly to clients | would bypass dataset authorization and payload validation
Confidence: high
Scope-risk: moderate
Directive: Keep graph payload edge properties backward-compatible; new fields should remain additive
Tested: ruff check touched files; targeted unit test suite (49 passed)
Not-tested: Live graph-engine integration for the new HTTP endpoint
